SP3 precise-ephemeris interpolation -> ECEF interop fixtures: provenance & licenses
===================================================================================

This directory holds an external-oracle cross-validation of kshana's SP3
precise-ephemeris position interpolation (kshana::sp3::Sp3Interpolator) against
RTKLIB, the de-facto open IGS reference. The pinned reference vectors
(sp3_ecef_reference.txt) are REAL RTKLIB output, produced by compiling RTKLIB
from C source and running it offline, so CI needs no runtime RTKLIB. See
generate_sp3_interp_reference.sh to reproduce.

WHAT IS VALIDATED
-----------------
RTKLIB's peph2pos()/pephpos() (src/preceph.c) is the de-facto IGS
precise-ephemeris interpolator. For each query time it selects the 11 tabulated
SP3 epochs (NMAX=10) bracketing it, rotates each node's ECEF position about +Z by
OMGE*(t_node - t_eval) -- the "correction for earh rotation ver.2.4.0" comment in
preceph.c -- so every node is expressed in the Earth-fixed frame at the SAME
evaluation instant, THEN fits an 11-point Neville polynomial. Without this node
correction a plain Lagrange fit on the raw ECEF samples disagrees with RTKLIB by
several centimetres at GNSS orbital velocity. kshana's Sp3Interpolator implements
the same Earth-rotation node correction and is checked to agree with RTKLIB
peph2pos to <= 1e-3 m per axis over 72 off-node SV-epochs.

