INPUT DATA: igs16296.sp3
------------------------
- Product : igs16296.sp3 -- IGS final combined precise GPS orbit product,
  GPS week 1629, day 6 (2011-04-02). Final orbit combination from the weighted
  average of cod/emr/esa/gfz/grg/jpl/mit/ngs/sio analysis centres, referenced to
  IGS time. 96 epochs on a 15-minute (900 s) grid, 32 GPS satellites, ECEF
  positions in km (SP3-c).
- Source (open) : RTKLIB's own committed test datum, util/data/igs16296.sp3 in
  github.com/tomojitakasu/RTKLIB at commit 71db0ffa (originally an IGS public
  CDDIS/IGS-archive product).
- Vendored bit-for-bit (the full file; the interior-epoch interpolation windows
  need the surrounding nodes, so no epochs are removed).
- SHA-256: ba56a435be22a192337d0f7fa41d37b988d1d5e20eef4a48070139de4ef16832
